I agree on both counts Meekrobe, Matter is absolutely lacking in terms of what it offers..something I sincerely hope Mythic does something about...and Matter spec is definitely more viable for a Cabbie than it is for a Sorcerer.<P>And Cozsorc, I respect your opinion.  And you are correct in that having a spec DoT that works out to do the same damage as the base dot is silly.  In my post I wrote:<P>"It works out to be about the same amount of damage in the end which in this case is a good thing (though this is also one of the primary things I feel should be fixed with the matter spec track..but thats another post...)."<P>Though I wouldn't characterize it as 120% broken, I do agree it needs work.  And as far as the damage output, the damage variance on the base line drains isn't that bad given the very low focus I place on training it.  If I am out to deal damage, chain casting my base line drains with their chance for criticals on top of a DoT pulsing at the upper limits of its damage range is not too shabby and has worked for me.  I will admit it is not for everyone...<P>--------------------<P>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<BR>Myrcil the Briton Matter Sorcerer<BR>Member of the Furious Pantaloons<BR>Galahad Server<BR>Member of the Sorcerer Testing Team in Beta<BR>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<P>"Who could ever calculate the path of a molecule?<BR>How do we know that the creations of worlds are not determined by falling grains of sand?"<BR>  --Victor Hugo, Les Miserables
