I think another concern I have in NOT keeping mind upto 'at least' 44 is:<P>I'm was 45 until last night-- (I have not tried mezzing at 46 yet), but was doign trees.  I have had about 36 mind spec at lvl 45, and the tress resist mez ~40% of the time on the first cast.<P>Now, I do NOT know if resists is strictly level based or if spec effects the resistance... BUT, Most of the mobs at the Trees are red++ and grape+++ to me when I was 45 (I suspect they will still be at 46).<P>So, if I having that bad of a resist rate with mind spec at 36, level 45... I would imaging that only have 34 mind at lvl 45 or 46 (Provided that SPEC effects resists) will be make it devistating for you to level once you start trees..<P>Now-- I might be completely wrong, and the player level is the only thing that effects resists, in which case, I still wouldn't go matter, but body if you stop mind at 34.<P>Personally, I'm taking mind to 44... personal choice.<P> -- Coz<P>--------------------<P>LvL 45 Sorcorer, Albion/Tristan<BR>LvL 41 Cleric, Albion/Tristan
