<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Wow, couple of great points raised so far.  Lets see if I can address a couple...<P>(If any of the original posters feel my quote skews the initial intent of the selection taken out of context, just let me know and I will try and clarifiy...)<P>First this from Naeen...<P>"How is the DoT more of a "fire and forget" spell than just throwing in a single body spec nuke?"<P>That is an excellent question! Let me try and explain the thought I had in mind when I typed that.  For starters, there are literally dozens of factors that effect my role in a group...am I the primary crowd controller?, are there other sorcerers in the group?, is there a minstrel in a group?...etc.  For the sake of this example, I will assume that I am the primary CC'er and the group is engaging mobs that exhibit BAF behavior.  My goal, in this hypothetical group, is to control the mobs that are not melee engaged.  Once I have successfully immobilized the extras, either by mez or by sending a pet to hold attention, then my next goal is to assist with damage dealing.  Now, for me, I am never really trying to be the one that deals the most damage...so long as I contribute in some way, I feel good about our victory.  Having a little bit experience in a primarily body spec'ed sorcerer, I know that the DD's cannot be cast too early in the fight or else you will draw aggro...and most likely die.  A fact that Naeen alludes to when he said, "I just have to wait a sec to cast it so I don't take aggro".  DoT's, however, I can cast early, and provided they stick, can forget about the mob for all intents and purposes and focus on my CC duty.  <P>In RvR, the fire and forget mentality gets translated into exactly what Cenergy describes when he wrote...<P>"In fights I can just cast my DOT on about 10 different people run back and watch the battle unfold. Since my DOT is hitting for 200+ at lvl 23, I just did over 2000 damage in that fight. That is alot of damage at my lvl and the mana drain is not that bad. It also brings me in some decent RP's."<P>One of my funniest RvR stories involves something very similar...it also happens to be one of my earliest.  I was in a keep re-taking group that had just liberated Benowyc and we got a crazy idea to check out the middy mile fort.  When we got there we ran through the gate and totally surprised a group of mids setting up to head out....not to mention they totally surprised us too...<P>The result was utter chaos...I was frantically hitting g, 1, 3 [target nearest enemy, /face, DoT].  I stuck DoT's on 4 peole in rapid succession amidst the mass of tons of fighting all around....my heart was pounding out of my chest.  I spotted a dwarf off on the side and ran towards him.  In my haste I didn't realize he was making spell casting motions...or I was too frantic to notice...and then BOOOOM, I blew up so hard I think my relatives in Texas felt it...I forget how much damage it did...but I know the next two times someone tried to rez me I died again due to the excess damage...<P>Anyway, at some point in all that I got 12 RP.  I don't remember how I got the points, but I talked about that encounter for a full week...it was so fun....I was laughing hysterically by the end...<P>But I digress....great points everyone...keep em coming.  Oh, one more thing, your Template, Malachi, is very interesting.  I would be very interested to hear the clever tactics you would devise to utilize the wide arsenal it would afford you...<P>--------------------<P>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<BR>Myrcil the Briton Matter Sorcerer<BR>Member of the Furious Pantaloons<BR>Galahad Server<BR>Member of the Sorcerer Testing Team in Beta<BR>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<P>"Who could ever calculate the path of a molecule?<BR>How do we know that the creations of worlds are not determined by falling grains of sand?"<BR>  --Victor Hugo, Les Miserables
