Jenlei, first, props for providing a well thought out, detailed post.<P>However, I still have to disagree with you.  Add either of the fixes you put in, and Matter is still god awful.  Why?  A few points of note, that I know have been discussed here before, but eh.<P>- DoT vs our DD.  DD is leaps and bounds more mana efficient, will not render a mez completely useless (until it becomes so anyway in the next patch.  le sigh), and will usually hit for more damage anyway, even without a crit.<P>- One spell a spec line does not make.  Obviously, there are other classes that are basically 1 spell spec, but there are at least other spells in the line that have SOME use.  The one, count em, one other spell in the line is a complete joke.<P>So anyway, increasing the potence of the DoT line isn't gonna cut it, IMNSFHO.  Matter needs a complete overhaul.  Start from scratch and add new spells from the ground up.  I honestly wouldn't even care *that* much if we weren't given a chance to re-spec.  At the very least, it would show that Mythic is paying attention to our poor class.<P>As a side note, me and my 29 Sorc on Guin are gonna tough it out.  I came very close to quitting, but I intend to be stubborn.  For better (ha!) or for worse (most likely), the Gimp will live on.  <P>Besides, it could be worse.  We could be Cabalists.    <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>- Aestus Prasinon<BR>- Saracen Sorcerer: Guinevere<BR>- Deus Vincit :Fear the Mint:
