<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Very good points, Aestus! <P>(This post is turning out far better than I had originally thought by the way...I fully expected to have to duck and cover the moment I hit the 'add post' button)<P>To answer your points,<P>"DoT vs our DD. DD is leaps and bounds more mana efficient, will not render a mez completely useless (until it becomes so anyway in the next patch. le sigh), and will usually hit for more damage anyway, even without a crit."<P>I personally feel that a lot depends on your own view of your sorcerer and how you envision him contributing in the virtual world.  I think the largest contributing factor to why you and I would tend to disagree is the fact that I do not consider my sorcerer primarily a damage dealer.  To me, I feel just as good after a fight if I have successfully kept all the mobs mezzed and all my group mates have survived as I would if I had drained, or DoT'ed them all to death.  Now, that does not mean I endorse that attitude for everyone, as a matter of fact, I am counting on the fact that others, including other sorcerers like Rizeo, are more focussed on damage dealing.  I see myself in more of a symbiotic role where I get the most exp and rp by helping my group to stay alive...and, also throwing in some not too shabby damage along the way.<P>When I solo, however, is when the damage output becomes key.  And is really the only time I imagine the ease of blowing something up at range.  But I have found more than enough tactics to allow me to be successful by myself both with and without a pet and still remaining primarily matter specced.<P>And your second point,<P>"One spell a spec line does not make. Obviously, there are other classes that are basically 1 spell spec, but there are at least other spells in the line that have SOME use. The one, count em, one other spell in the line is a complete joke."<P>I absolutely 100% agree with this as well as your elaboration that follows.  Matter needs fixing in a big way.   What I offered was a way to fix the silliness of the base and spec dots doing the same amount of damage for a 2/3 spec matter sorcerer.  That, of course, is only one facet of the, as you correctly put it, 'overhaul' that needs to take place with the spec line.<P>--------------------<P>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<BR>Myrcil the Briton Matter Sorcerer<BR>Member of the Furious Pantaloons<BR>Galahad Server<BR>Member of the Sorcerer Testing Team in Beta<BR>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<P>"Who could ever calculate the path of a molecule?<BR>How do we know that the creations of worlds are not determined by falling grains of sand?"<BR>  --Victor Hugo, Les Miserables
