<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
DOTs actually help with aggro in many cases. The fire and forget nature comes into play when they do not interrupt what else you can do while they are still working. You can apply a DOT and STILL blast... now your DOT damage is added each round on top of your blasts.<P>Back in BETA the matter was was the do all and end all of both Cabbies AND Sorcerors. Not even the mighty paladin, nor the horribly overpowered fire wizard could compare with what we could do. Soloing 2 or 3 reds at a time with no pet was commonplace.<P>...alas, things have changed.<P>But the pendulum has swung too far the other way. Matter is indeed an underdeveloped line. this does NOT mean the spells in the line are useless. We could not survive without the matter line, but speccing to gain abilities in the telekinesis line is less than spectacular. Spec used to increase the effectiveness of our self buffs, that was changed. DOTs used to layer, that was changed (and this one I 100% agree with). But after some logical realignment of the spells, matter is left wanting.<P>We can all agree on this, but this does not mean the spells in the matter line are useless, far from it.<P>My general spec path is one that allows me to do everything a sorceror is capable of reasonably well. I am not a weak wizzy who mezzes, I am not a weak cabby who cannot summon. I am a sorceror. The end result is Mind 34, Body 30 and Matter 29.<P>Now of prime importance to me is keeping an even con pet. Then I split all points fairly evenly between the other 2 specs. I will change depending on if a key spell will become available one way or the other.<P>The reason 30 Body is important for me is the AE root, but this is far mroe important in RvR than PvE to me. <P>DOTs are frequently resisted less than my other weapons. Enemys cannot run out of DOT range once it is applied. And I can still be doing damage to help the gorup without drawing aggro, or having to take my attention off the CC duties.<P>And there is not much more satisfying than DOTing the assassin who tried to kill you, watching him run back to the safety of his guards, and still dropping dead before your eyes.<P>Also, the DOT damage was something i tried to have addressed long ago. They adjusted it some but not enough IMO. The advanced specs do the same amount of damage per tick, but for 2 tickls longer. this only applies if you are almost completely Matter spec though. If the line was worth total dedication, this would be great. The spec level DOTs need to be scaled to be earned 1/3 earlier to match the baseline DOTs on a per tick damage basis. this would open it up and have the last 15 to 20 levels add some truly devastating DOTs.<P>But ya know what? The entire focus of the spec has always been 2/3 of your level. Why spells were added above elvel 30 i don't know, but the whole 2/3 balance is thrown out the window when there are spells ABOVE lev 30 spec that you really need (want) for your class. The level 32 charm is a prime example. To remain capable we HAVE to go over the 2/3 spec target. The spec level spells shoudl have topped out at 30, and anything higher shoudl have only been gained in baseline.<P>....but I digress....<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...<P>Please visit our <A HREF="http://www.yesterdayland.com/popopedia/shows/toys/ty1050.php" TARGET=_blank>Sponsors!</A>  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">
