Well Battik, Meek, whatever your play style.  Some things make more sense than others, but what's important is enjoying it.  I've heard Archers whine that they're bored because they can only do one thing: one-hit Crit even con Mages.  It's damned effective....but highly boring to some of them.<P>So what matters is enjoying your work, however you choose to do it.  <P>For arguementative purposes...for both the stealther and the 4 people idea.  First, on the stealther one, a DoT makes certain they don't stealth for the amount of time it takes.  Sicking your pet on it is nice, but what about when we die within the first 15 seconds of a fight, as many Sorcerers do?  Then their pet walks off, and the Stealther can go back to work.  Same with the four people, even if we die the DoT keeps ticking.  Now I know you can do the same amount faster with a DD....but it's at least possible, if that's your style, to try using DoTs since, by Meek's admission, we aren't expected to do major amounts of damage (think it was meant for PvE, but it applies somewhat to RvR as well, to some extent, yes?)<P>There's probably a definate answer out there somewhere about which is technically more efficient, more sensible, etc.  But if you enjoy doing what you do, then by all means, let no sensibilities or efficiencies stop you from enjoying.
</FONT>
