<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
You are wrong Stellaris, the original post was not just about how much the poster enjoyed playing a matter specced sorcerer.<BR>It actually implied that by using dots the sorcerer could provide better CC. Which of course is simply not true. Calling a DoT a "fire and forget" spell is kind of funny to me. Are nukes not fire and forget? If you have problems drawing aggro using nukes then maybe you are just nuking too early. <P>Ok, stealther attacks, send your pet and dot if you are that worried about it. You do not need to have specced matter to do that. <P>I ma not sure what the "4 person idea" is, unless you mean the switching targets and dotting. In that case your nukes are doing as much damage as the dot would and all at once. The faster the damage in rvr the better, actually in pve too. If you die while switchig targets and dotting you have to stop doing that just as if you were killed when nuking.<P>I don't care how anyone speccs, if you want to go 50 matter go for it     <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> But, the original post was trying to point out the advantages of speccing matter when in reality the negatives far out weigh the positives. In fact after reading the post I still could not see any positives for speccing matter.<P>Battik
