<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Fire and forget exclusively refers to soemthing you activate, then it continues to work and do it's job without any further attention from you. A blast does NOT ualify, becuase after the blast it is doing nothing else, hence DOTs and Debuffs are Fire and Forget, DDs are not.<P>Of utmost importance to me is range... range is everything in this game. And if you apply a DOT to a target, the range you can continue dealing damage to them has beome infinite. I always break a Mez with a DOT in RvR. Then there are 2 options. they charge me and my pet and blasts can whittle them down, or they run away, and my DOT continues to do damage while my pet chases. Normally it is the DOT that drops their health enough to lower their run speed and they MUSt turn to face my pet, with no END.<P>The DOT is the primary form of damage I apply in RvR. Before the Pet, before the DD, always the DOT.<P>I don't see hwo anyone can not understand the Fire and forget comment made here. I can't understand how anyone can't see the inherent bonus when your target runs out of range, or goes stealth, and you can STILL be doing damage to them.<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...<P>Please visit our <A HREF="http://www.yesterdayland.com/popopedia/shows/toys/ty1050.php" TARGET=_blank>Sponsors!</A>  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">
